dspace-development.title: `null` Bitstreams are appended (erroneously) for DataSpace Items

comments.body: It appears that there are cases where the Bitstream uploads failed to process, please see https://dataspace.princeton.edu/bitstream/88435/dsp01kp78gj856/3/ and https://dataspace.princeton.edu/handle/88435/dsp01kp78gj856
Using ad-hoc queries in PostgreSQL, I am finding that there are Bitstreams missing for these Items.

The Bundles do exist for the case of https://dataspace.princeton.edu/handle/88435/dsp01kp78gj856:

- 98533
- 98567
- 98566
Updating the Bitstream metadata seems to have fixed these Item records. I shall proceed with contacting the reporting user in order to identify any other outstanding Items.

figgy.title: Is it possible to get a report generated for all image counts for items ingested as part of the patron requests collection in figgy?
Character encoding failure on images generated from PDF

comments.body: Joshua Seufert suggested that we try converting the PDFs to PDF/A format before ingesting, and this solved the problem!  I replaced the problematic files so the link cited above no longer shows the issue.  We don't have any other issues with this item, but if you still want to investigate the original issue, please let me know and I can prove the original unconverted file.
That's great! I'll go ahead and close this since you found an acceptable workaround.

@pmgreen could you fill in some details here about the current process. I believe Alma can publish to Kbart.

Basically run a simple Ruby script to:
- fetch and loop through files in the weekly (every Monday) kbart extract in $SFXLCL41/dbs/scratch
- extract the target name from each filename and add them to a combined output file
- ftp the resulting file to the access anywhere server
